[h2 id=Tricks&Glitches-Bothgames 
	"Tricks & Glitches - Both games
	$LF
]h2
[pre 
	$LF
]pre
[h3 id=HUDOffGlitch 
	"HUD Off Glitch 
	(youtube|v=z5qPiGqPVtI)
	" 
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"When the HUD menus open, you can click the NPCs with the cursor juuust when the HUD menu is starting to open (Frame specific), not when its fully open or when its not opening at all. After you talk to them, the Gadget or Item menu will get stuck. The Gadget menu will not work properly, but the Item menu will do. This does save time both in real time and in TAS time.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"NOTE:
	]b
	" This glitch doesn't work with the Puffle selection menu due to a different structure in gameplay and loading bytes in their address code. 
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Skippingtext 
	"Skipping text
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Every textbox has a specific set of frames when you can skip a dialogue box.
	$LF
	"In Herbert's Revenge, its always a 10 frame window in order to skip a dialogue box (unless the room you're in is lagging when you're skipping text), and there are very rare instances where you can skip them earlier, if the textbox has a [...] on the lower right corner of the box.
	$LF
	"Skipping text in the Original EPF however, is quite a bit different. It's 3x times slower than Herbert's Revenge for some strange reason, being 30 frames instead of 10, and there's no known way to speed up the process of skipping text in that game so far.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Fade-InClicks 
	"Fade-In Clicks
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"You can click on NPCs and everything else before the fade-in transitions in game. Those screens are very specific and cannot be performed every single time. You can only perform them when starting a mission or quitting a minigame or even quitting your clothing and objectives screens.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=Fade-OutClicks 
	"Fade-Out Clicks
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Like the above trick, you can do this on very specific transitions too. Only this time you have limited time to do something.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"NOTE:
	]b
	" Maybe can performed on the Map too...(for both tricks)
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=DesicionBoxTimings 
	"Desicion Box Timings
	$LF
]h3
[pre 
	"TODO: Add gif to this thing.
	$LF
]pre
[div class=p 
	"Theres a frame perfect trick that saves time during a dialog. When hitting the first or second decision in a decision box selection on a specific timing, you'll save frames depending on the 1st or 2nd choice box. (You can't do this on the 3rd choice box).
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=ClickXClickMovement 
	"Click X Click Movement
	$LF
]h3
[pre 
	"TODO: Add gif to this too...
	$LF
]pre
[div class=p 
	"Movement in-screen is also helpful, clicking the cursor in a different location is faster than moving it to that location. Also this involves clicking on NPCs and locations too, with a correct frame rule.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=InstantItem/GadgetAction 
	"Instant Item/Gadget Action
	$LF
]h3
[pre 
	"TODO: Add gif to this again...
	$LF
]pre
[div class=p 
	"Its faster to click on the item/gadget and click on its location again (also includes combining items), than dragging (holding the touch screen) the item/gadget to its proper location
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"This also involves the Map, by clicking on a Map location multiple times than just clicking it once.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	[b 
		"NOTE:
	]b
	" Dragging items is faster on the Item Menu, double click is faster on the Gadget Menu.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=LayerSkipperGlitch 
	"Layer Skipper Glitch
	$LF
]h3
[pre 
	"TODO: Add gif image of the glitch in action.
	$LF
]pre
[div class=p 
	"Using an Elite Puffle, you can hit blocked objects by passing through a specific sprite layer between the blocked object and the HUD. The game was not fully programmed to detect this bug that saves time depending on the situation.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=PuffleScrollingGlitch(FastestCameraMovement) 
	"Puffle Scrolling Glitch (Fastest Camera Movement) 
	(youtube|v=0DChVsMBZeE)
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"This glitch involves a HUD menu, and pressing the D-pad to move the cursor.
	$LF
	"When moving the cursor enough with the D-pad with a HUD menu open, the cursor will move outside from the camera and the game will not follow it. When the HUD menu closes and you stop moving the cursor, the camera will freeze and it will not move at all, unless you use the touch screen to move the cursor and every thing will get back to normal.
	$LF
	"But if you close the HUD menu while moving the D-pad to the left or right, the camera will get launched and it will scroll the screen really fast, faster than any normal way. The glitch will get cancel when the cursor is on screen again, so be careful with that.
	$LF
	"This saves time mostly on not rotational rooms in the game (Rarely on rotational ones).
	$LF
]div
